</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="202" pageNumber="480" type="breeding">
<paragraph blockId="202.[190,1395,2740,3285]" pageId="202" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[191,323,3015,3048]" pageId="202" pageNumber="480">Breeding.</emphasis>
Philip Myers’s Grass Mice are reproductively active during summer and at least until the middle of autumn (January-May). Females carry three or more embryos.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[190,1207,3094,3127]" pageId="202" pageNumber="480" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="202.[190,1395,2740,3285]" box="[190,1207,3094,3127]" pageId="202" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[190,425,3094,3127]" pageId="202" pageNumber="480">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
Philip Myers’s Grass Mouse is terrestrial and nocturnal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
